A school proprietor, Mr. Patrick Kogbodi, has been reportedly kidnapped by gunmen on Sunday morning in Ughelli, Delta state. According to sources, Kogbodi was abducted about 8am on his way to church. The Nation gathered that the kidnappers intercepted his vehicle and whisked him to an unknown location. The victim is the founder of a private school, Kogbodi International School along Taiga Street off the Ughelli/Warri Expressway. Delta Commissioner of police, Mr. Adeyinka Adeleke, confirmed the report. He said: “We are aware,” of the case.